-- Copper Declines 0.2% to $6,620 a Metric Ton, Reversing Earlier Advance
-- Xiaowei Li
-- 2010-07-13T02:12:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/copper-declines-0-2-to-6-620-a-metric-ton-reversing-earlier-advance.html

          
          
             Copper for three-month delivery on
the London Metal Exchange dropped 0.2 percent to $6,620 a metric
ton, reversing an earlier 0.9 percent gain.  
